  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A severely reduced left ventricular ejection fraction is associated with increased mortality
      due to pump failure as well as to malignant ventricular arrhythmia. We hypothesize that
      targeted training may lead to improved survival and to increased parameters of risk
      stratification for malignant arrhythmia. Additionally, the training may lead to an improved
      psychological and mental condition of the patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
